  • Ar_Becker_2009

Ar_Becker_2009¶

The considered RKM takes into account electrons, the argon atom ground state \(\mathrm{Ar[1p_0]}\), the argon atom ion \(\mathrm{Ar}^\mathrm{+}\), and argon atoms in a lumped excited state \(\mathrm{Ar}^\mathrm{*}\). The lumped excited state represents two metastable states of the argon atom \(\mathrm{Ar[1s]}_\mathrm{5}\) and \(\mathrm{Ar[1s]}_\mathrm{3}\). The details about the transport coefficients of the included species and the rate coefficients of the considered chemical reactions can be found in Becker et al. (M. Becker, D. Loffhagen, W. Schmidt, Comput. Phys. Commun. 180 (8) (2009) 1230).
